HOMEOWNER'S INSURANCE POLICY
Policy Number: HO-2024-001
Effective Date: January 1, 2025

SECTION I - COVERAGE SUMMARY
This policy provides coverage for your dwelling, personal property, liability, and medical payments to others. Coverage amounts are shown in your declarations page.

SECTION II - DWELLING COVERAGE
We cover the dwelling on the residence premises shown in the declarations. The dwelling includes structures attached to the dwelling and outdoor equipment permanently installed and used exclusively to service the dwelling.

SECTION III - PERSONAL PROPERTY COVERAGE  
We cover personal property owned or used by an insured while it is anywhere in the world. Personal property in the usual location for that type of property is covered for the perils insured against. Personal property while away from the residence premises is covered for the perils insured against except for certain exclusions.

SECTION IV - LIABILITY COVERAGE
If a claim is made or a suit is brought against an insured for damages because of bodily injury or property damage to which this coverage applies, we will pay up to our limit of liability for damages for which an insured is legally liable. We will also provide a defense at our expense by counsel of our choice.

SECTION V - MEDICAL PAYMENTS COVERAGE
We will pay the necessary medical expenses incurred or medically ascertained within three years from the date of an accident causing bodily injury. Medical expenses means reasonable charges for medical, surgical, x-ray, dental, ambulance, hospital, professional nursing, prosthetic devices and funeral services.

SECTION VI - EXCLUSIONS
We do not insure for loss caused directly or indirectly by any of the following: Earth movement, including earthquake, landslide, mudflow, earth sinking, rising or shifting; Flood, surface water, waves, tidal water, overflow of a body of water, or spray from any of these, all whether driven by wind or not; War, including undeclared war, civil war, insurrection, rebellion or revolution.

SECTION VII - CONDITIONS
Loss Settlement: Covered property losses are settled at actual cash value at the time of loss but not more than the amount required to repair or replace. Claims Procedure: In case of a loss, you must see that the following duties are performed.

SECTION VIII - DEDUCTIBLES
The deductible amount shown in the declarations applies to each loss and is deducted from the amount of loss before any payment is made. Only one deductible applies regardless of the number of coverages involved in the loss.
